==English==
===Etymology===
*[[w:French language|French]] 1882 ''péjorative'' "depreciative, disparaging", from [[w:Vulgar Latin|Late Latin]] ''pejoratus'', past participle of ''pejorare'' "make worse", from [[w:Latin|Latin]] ''pejor'' "worse"
*<u>related</u>: English 1644 ''pejorate'' "to worsen", from [[w:Vulgar Latin|Late Latin]] ''pejoratus'', past participle of ''pejorare'' "make worse", from [[w:Latin|Latin]] ''pejor'' "worse"
===Pronunciation===
/pɪˈdʒɒrətɪv/
===Noun===
'''pejorative'''
#a [[disparaging]], [[belittling]] or [[derogatory]] word or expression

